INFLUENZA (17): MEXICO, KOSOVO, PERU, CASE SURGE
************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

In this update:
[1] Mexico
[2] Kosovo
[3] Peru (Piura): alert

******
[1] Mexico
Date: Sat 26 Mar 2016
Source: APA [edited]
http://en.apa.az/-_241158.html


Mexico has seen a sharp jump in cases of the [influenza A(H1N1) virus], popularly known as swine flu, killing 95 people in the past week, RIA Novosti [news agency] reported.

The total number of deaths from flu cases since October 2015 has increased to 372. Of them, 278 people died of swine flu.

Mexico has reported 8000 cases of infection by various influenza viruses.

Earlier, the Mexican government emphasized schools should not shut their doors due to the flu, however, many private kindergartens and schools before the start of the spring break decided to suspend classes.

